        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47312",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Kim, I've cleaned up your patch a little (modified formatting and output messages to match existing code, removed some unnecessary lines) and added code to remove the {{layoutsDirectory}} entry from {{.zfproject.xml}} when {{zf disable layout}} is called. \r\n\r\nI've attached the patch, and will commit it soon.  Can you try it out for me first to make sure the changes I added are OK?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-29T22:44:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-29T23:05:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47319",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Adam,\r\n\r\nI will try this later but it seems like the layout directory is deleted too. I think we don't want to do that. A good layout may end up to be deleted accidentally. There should be a separate action for this, for example {{zf remove layout}}.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-30T05:11:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-30T05:11:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47329",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Adam,\r\n\r\nI have now tested your patch. I see that it only removes these lines from {{.zfproject.xml}}\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n<layoutsDirectory>\r\n  <layoutScriptsDirectory>\r\n    <layoutScriptFile layoutName=\"layout\"\/>\r\n  <\/layoutScriptsDirectory>\r\n<\/layoutsDirectory>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nand leaves the {{\/application\/layouts}} directory untouched. It's good that it really does not remove that directory. However, the {{.zfproject.xml}} is now out of sync what's the real directory structure. I still think that disabling layout should only remove the layout resource from {{application\/configs\/application.ini}} and leave the project structure untouched - including {{.zfproject.xml}}.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-30T14:26:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-30T14:26:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47331",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with Kim on this -- disabling is not the same as removing, and I'd worry that re-enabling later would try to overwrite files.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of which: what happens when you call \"zf enable layout\" after calling \"zf disable layout\"? I would expect in this case the following:\r\n\r\n* \"disable\" would remove or comment out the application.ini entry\r\n* \"enable\" after a disable would add or uncomment the application.ini entry, and check to see if a <layoutsDirectory> entry exists; if not, it creates it. It also checks to see if the layout.phtml file exists; if so, it does nothing, but if not, it creates it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-06-30T14:47:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-06-30T14:47:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47364",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Valid point; I hadn't considered that .zfproject.xml would end up out of sync with the actual project directory structure. \r\n\r\nIn the patch I attached {{zf disable layout}} removes the layout config entry from application.ini and associated layout information from .zfproject.xml, but leaves the layout scripts intact.\r\n\r\nWhen you call {{zf enable layout}} after calling {{zf disable layout}} it will add the {{resources.layout.layoutPath}} entry in [production] section.  Unless run in pretend mode, {{zf enable layout}} always calls {{Zend_Tool_Project_Provider_Layout::createResource}}, which updates the .zfproject.xml file with the structure Kim outlined in his comment on 30\/Jun\/2011 @ 2:26PM.  If i'm reading the code correctly, then {{zf enable layout}} will always overwrite the existing layout script file, ( {{Zend_Tool_Project_Provider_Layout::enable}} always calls {{$layoutScriptFile->create()}})\r\n\r\nShould we consider changing that behaviour? ie: {{zf disable layout}} comments out layout lines in application.ini, {{zf enable layout}} enables commented-out lines (or creates new ones if they don't already exist) and doesn't overwrite an existing layout file\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-05T15:45:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-05T15:46:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47786",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Matthew\r\nBased on your comments I have rejigged the fix:\r\n* Don't overwrite an existing layout file when calling {{zf enable layout}} after {{zf disable layout}}\r\n* Don't remove {{layoutsDirectory}} tree from .zfproject.xml\r\n\r\nShould we also implement a {{zf remove layout}} function as Kim mentioned above, ie: deletes all traces of {{zf enable layout}} having ever been run?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-30T00:29:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-30T00:29:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47787",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fix committed to trunk in r24303",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-30T00:33:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-30T00:33:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47798",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Adam - looks like you really fix it. I was struggling with the following use case, but you fix it ...\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nzf create project ZF-11516\r\ncd ZF-11516\r\nzf enable layout\r\nzf disable layout\r\nrm application\/layouts\/scripts\/layout.phtml\r\nzf enable layout # should create layout.phtml\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nbq. Should we also implement a zf remove layout function as Kim mentioned above, ie: deletes all traces of zf enable layout having ever been run?\r\n\r\nI think that it's not a good idea to delete all traces of zf enable layout. For example, one may have multiple layout files under {{application\/layouts\/scripts}}. Thus zf remove layout should take additional parameter to tell the tool which layout file will be removed etc. Because of this additional overhead, I wouldn't implement this function as we don't know do we really need this - or what do you think?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-30T07:29:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-30T07:29:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48224",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank you both for your feedback.  I've merged the fix into release-1.11 in r24408\r\n\r\nAs for a {{zf remove layout}}, I'm fine with omitting it.  I didn't see a solid use case for it, but if you did I would have implemented it anyway. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-08-26T22:07:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-08-26T22:07:36.000+0000"
                },
